<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Abs is the % of hits that your armor will infact absorb the hit totally. So basically going from say 5% (Being hit 95% of the time) to say 15% (Being hit for 85%) of the time is better but still need more HP OR AF for the other 85%.<P> 1 hit = death <P><BR> AF = Total Dmg done per hit<BR> Abs = % an armor/item will absorb the total blow.<P> I am not saying casters should be invunerable but we have neither the spell dmg output nor even the specialized spell lines to even say the spell casters have a chance to live.<P> We are now equivalent to leather armor which is nice but even the lowest leather class has a TON of more hp's then us.<P><BR> So if you want to RvR and live make sure you have some nice cleric friends who do not mind keeping u buffed  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> (then u could last 2 hits  <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> )
</FONT>
