<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Going after a Cleric, unless very low in /con to the attacker, is crazy.  Clerics can be very very tough to kill.  A Cleric who has both heals available is NOT a good opponent for an Archer, unless again, is a very low con.<P>I speak from experience.  Most of the time I play I have two accounts active: 43 Sorc and a 41 Cleric.  I even often PvP with the 41 Cleric permanently /following the Sorc.  The advantage to me: I get two instant heals and good buffs.  It doesn't take a lot of effort to lean over to the 2nd computer and tap an instant heal key.  That being said my Sorc is still generally the one taken out first since he's by far the biggest offensive threat.  When the Sorc is jumped the life span is usually measured in 5-10 seconds.  Conversely the same people usually turn onto my Cleric who normally lasts 20 seconds or sometimes longer.  If I were actively playing the Cleric I'd last much longer I'm sure since he wouldn't have been standing around with his thumb up it to begin with.<P>The few times when an Archer has attacked my Cleric (usually on his way to res my Sorc) have resulted in an Archer running away.  If I have friends with me it results in a dead Archer (/thanks Stun).<P>This doesn't add a whole lot to the discussion other than Clerics are very durable compared to Sorcs =).<P>As far as how much damage is absorbed I honestly have no idea how good it will be, but it certainly can't hurt.  Just keep in mind how fast Scouts and Friars tend to get owned by mobs in melee as a method of comparison.  <P>Rayne
