<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
No, Armor used to be listed as a total aggregate of AF and ABS. Now it is combined in the main stat window, but still lited as AF and ABS on each individual item.<P>AF is like the D&D AC, it is most definately avoidance. Casters have always buffed their avoidance, or worn armor that added to avoidance. When we do get hit, we feel it.<P>It is not the absorption rate, or else there woudl be no stat named absorption!  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> BUt, this is not the final way it works is the problem. AF, or avoidance, inherently has the chance to avoid portions of the damage also, or every hit would do Max damage if it connected. So it seems AF has SOME ABS type component, but it is still mainly avoidance. <P>ABS on the other hand cannot cause the hit to miss, but it can drastically enhance the amount the attack is lessened when successful. So it seems to add to the Inherent ABS of AF.<P>This make any sense?<P>The total is an aggregate of the AF and ABS They have enver released the specifics, but the closest I can come in generalities is this....<P>AF = Avoidance and Reduction<BR>ABS = a bonus to the reduction alone<P>So AF+ABS= Avoid -- <BR>and if hit <BR>Damage= Dam*(inherent Abs+Abs bonus)<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
