<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
One other item to add to your fine explanation i3ullseye. If enough of the damage is absorbed by the ABS component so that the damage remaining is &lt;= 0, the attack is registered as a miss. It really wasn't a miss of course, but the code makes it one when there's no more damage to dole out. This fact will confuse log parsing programs which are not aware of the difference between a clean miss and damage &lt; 0.<P>--------------------<P>Nemus Imzadi <BR>Saracen Sorcerer <BR>Knight of Virtue<BR>Champions of Virtue, Bedevere <BR>www.championsofvirtue.com
</FONT>
